Evergreen Solar Reaches Record Low in Fifth Straight Decline

-- B y   E h r e n   G o o s s e n s
-- 
2011-05-23T15:59:03Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-23/evergreen-solar-reaches-record-low-in-fifth-straight-decline.html
Evergreen Solar Inc. (ESLR) , a maker of
solar photovoltaic cells and panels, fell for a fifth straight
day and reached a record low.  The company droped as much as 19 cents, or 21 percent, to
71 cents in Nasdaq Stock Market trading. It was at 78 cents,
down 13 percent, at 11:52 a.m. in New York. That’s the lowest
price since the company went public in November 2000 and the
biggest decline since May 13. The Boston Globe reported May 20
that the company would lose some state tax benefits in
 Massachusetts .  The Marlboro, Massachusetts-based company’s shares have
lost 78 percent of their value this year.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ehren Goossens in  New York  at 
